[h2 id=LevelCommentsFromTakz 
	"Level comments (from takz)
	$LF
]h2
[h4 id=AngelIsland 
	"Angel Island
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"It turns out Knuckles can do the second loop zip and jump higher without hitting the wall in Act 1. Managed to get a sub-40 in the end. Act 2 remains the same.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Hydrocity1 
	"Hydrocity 1
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"71 frames saved. 40 were lost from preparing the death in Act 2 by deactivating the walk on water object and this gained 111 frames.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Hydrocity2 
	"Hydrocity 2
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"32 frames were saved from a new route I took in the loopback section of Act 2. After climbing the wall I glided to the tube and spindashed my way up before the camera stopped at the horizontal point of the boss. I managed to get the first hit whilst gliding towards the boss and then landed all 7 frame perfect hits.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=MarbleGarden12 
	"Marble Garden 1+2
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"30 frames were saved from getting to the slope quicker. It's still slower than Sonic's run by 1 frame.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=CarnivalNight1 
	"Carnival Night 1
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Faster route before the level wrap by jumping next to the spikes and spindashing and jumping into them sending Knuckles through the ground.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=IceCap 
	"Ice Cap
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Sub-39. I still was not able to get to the end boundary on time.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=LaunchBase 
	"Launch Base
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Still no improvement in Act 1.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Act 2 was the biggest improvement in the Sonic 3 half due to a few strats such as clipping through the slope to get to the tube faster (found by Kaan). On top of that, the boss was improved by a lot as I managed to deliver the first 8 hits and let the Beam Rocket boss go off screen and appear on the left side and delivered the last hit.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=MushroomHill1 
	"Mushroom Hill 1
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"16 frames saved from an improved level wrap and a faster boss. Also managed to get a sub-30:xx time as well.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=MushroomHill2 
	"Mushroom Hill 2
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Improved zip to the giant ring room.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=FlyingBattery1 
	"Flying Battery 1
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"If you compare this to the 2017 run, I basically saved 44 frames from the new boss method and another 23 frames for the new level wrap route found by Kaan55. How this works is that Knuckles has to be sent at least at a speed faster than 16 pixels (4096 subpixels) to the left for the level wrap to work and the horizontal position in the last frame before the wrap must be 16(pixel):1(subpixel) or further to the right. In this run, the last position before the wrap was 16(p):13(sp) while the speed was 4144 subpixels/frame which allowed the level wrap to happen. I tried the same thing with Sonic and Tails but no luck for them although to be fair each character now has their own way to level wrap to the end due to new strats that have been found.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=FlyingBattery2 
	"Flying Battery 2
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Managed to improve the vertical zip to the top of the boundary but still slower than Sonic by 6 frames.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Sandopolis2 
	"Sandopolis 2
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Kaan55 completed this level saving 599 frames from my improved time of 0:58.28. This time save came from several new routes such as gliding through the barrel leading into a zip at the start, clipping through slopes and a boss route similar to the Sonic any% run except a bit slower.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=LavaReef 
	"Lava Reef
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"I had to redo this zone multiple times because the level kept desyncing at the end of the Act 1 boss. 4 frames were lost because I positioned the boss at the same place as the fire monitor's position.
	$LF
